        {
          "titre": "Once you have developed a solid foundation of Sila and of Right View through studying these texts; it is time to join a",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "Sangha, to give alms, to receive instruction in meditation from a monk, if you want to become a serious practitioner. It is",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "important to develop View before this point, and to rely on the suttas because monks are fallible and cannot be relied on as",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "ultimate authority when it comes to the Dhamma (the only ultimate authority in Buddhism is, as you might imagine: the",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "Buddha). With Right View you will be able to stay vigilant of any suspicious \"Dhamma\" which deviates from what the",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "Buddha taught. This is not to say that you must find a \"perfect teacher,\" even flawed teachers have much to offer, as long",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "as the student knows when to potentially discard something (that contradicts the suttas) and what teachings to keep from",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "their teacher. This applies to all sects, all traditions. If you are being taught something with strong basis in the suttas, it",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "is Buddhadhamma. All sects have revisions and quirks, but at the same time all sects have great wisdom to offer,",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "especially when they help illuminate teachings in the suttas that might have gone over the students' head. This is why",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "this chart is meant to be non-sectarian and early Buddhist. Remember, Sila before Samadhi, and may this chart be for the",
          "auteur": null,
          "tier": null
        },
        {
          "titre": "may all beings be free from suffering.",
          "auteur": "benefit of all beings",
          "tier": null
        }
